      "word": "저",
      "romanized": "jeo",
      "grammarNote": "저 (jeo) = formal/polite 'I'. 나 (na) = casual 'I' with friends. Always use 저 with strangers or elders. In polite speech, 저는 pairs with 해요-style verbs; 나는 pairs with casual speech.",
